Yes, you can do something like this:

```rust
fn main() {
    let bindings = bindgen::Builder::default()
        .header("path/to/your/header.h")
        .allowlist_function("some_safe_func")
        .blocklist_type("UnsafeStruct")
        .generate()
        .expect("Unable to generate bindings");

    bindings.write_header("bindings.rs").unwrap();
}
